The paper presents a novel optimization method for meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on a family of meta-learning methods for neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since these sub-categories are closely related to machine learning. Additionally, the paper mentions using natural language processing tasks as an example, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper uses gradient-based optimization, which is a common technique in neural networks, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
